\subsection{Conrey index of a Dirichlet character}
\begin{definition}\label{character.dirichlet.conrey.index}
\uses{character.dirichlet,character.dirichlet.conrey,character.dirichlet.modulus}
The **Conrey index** (or **index**) of a {{KNOWL('character.dirichlet', 'Dirichlet character')}} $\chi$ of {{KNOWL('character.dirichlet.modulus', 'modulus')}} $q$ is the unique positive integer $n < \max(q,2)$ for which $\chi = \chi_q(n,\cdot)$ in the {{KNOWL('character.dirichlet.conrey', 'Conrey labeling system')}}.
\end{definition}


